Author: TonyL#3577
Content:
Hi @eclips 
There is a `pagesTotal":12` returning in JSON

Author: TonyL#3577
Content: To fetch first page you have to call like a `https://explorer.komodo.services/api/txs/?address=RLjJ8upp93NjeMVbhjVHCXiFVrq8zWo3GT&pageNum=0`

Author: TonyL#3577
Content: Second page `&pageNum=1` and etc

Author: eclips#1570
Content: meaning i only get the first page by default ?

Author: TonyL#3577
Content: There is page length set in transactions.js on explorer sourcecode side. So it's dividing return on pages depends of value of `var pageLength = <amountoftxs> ` And by default you get only first page.

Author: eclips#1570
Content: ok

Author: TonyL#3577
Content: So you have to implement some for loop to go through all the pages

Author: TonyL#3577
Content: I guess

Content: that was my next question

Author: eclips#1570
Content: so now way to have it all with 1 URL ?

Author: TonyL#3577
Content: Change `var pageLength =` in the explorer sourcecode only way to have it all with 1 URL I think

Author: eclips#1570
Content: guess i'll have to do some scripting

Author: TonyL#3577
Content: Otherwise you have to execute and append to your JSON: https://explorer.komodo.services/api/txs/?address=RLjJ8upp93NjeMVbhjVHCXiFVrq8zWo3GT&pageNum=<I> for each page from 0 to pagesTotal-1

Author: TonyL#3577
Content: And then send this JSON where you need

Content:
Hi, is a wallet created using `getnewaddress` on an assetchain (ie. komodo-cli  -ac_name=STAKED4) the same as wallet created running `komodod`?

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: privkey/pubkey pairs are always the same. whether it is in any specific wallet depends only on whether it is in that wallet

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: a wallet is basically a collection of privkeys
